FBIS3-47133 "dreas006_c_94006" FBIS-EAS-94-006 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Jan 1994 North Korea PRC Premier's Remarks on Nuclear Issue Cited SK1001051294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0501 GMT 10 Jan 94 SK1001051294 Pyongyang KCNA Language: English Article Type:BFN ["Chinese Premier Favors Negotiated Solution of Nuclear Problem" -- KCNA headline] [Text] Pyongyang, January 10 (KCNA) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng at a talk with the Japanese foreign minister Saturday emphasized that the nuclear problem on the Korean peninsula would be resolved through negotiations, according to a XINHUA report. Li said China supports the non-nuclear proposal and stability and peace there. "We oppose any coercive way or embargo, which will inevitably make the problem more complicated," Li said.
